<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.5–15.4; head length: 1.4–2.0; head width: 3.1–3.5; pronotal length: 2.5–2.9; pronotal width: 8.9–9.5.3; scutellum length: 6.7–7.4; scutellum width: 5.0–5.5; abdominal width: 8.0–8.7; length of antennal segments. I: 1.0; II: 1.1–2.0; III: 1.2–2.9; IV: 4.2–4.4; V: missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all of its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1338,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[531,633,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with brown lines (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1131,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1350,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with lateral sides somewhat excavated (
<figureCitation box="[663,786,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim with a small median excavation at the base of the proctiger (
<figureCitation box="[307,395,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup laminar, thick, rounded distally, with a small step at the base, and adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[700,823,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere elongated, club-like, strongly bent laterally; inner margin with conspicuous carina ending at the apex of the posterior lobe; posterior lobe large and acuminated distally; anterior lobe rounded and barely developed; stalk conspicuously carinated (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1205,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3A–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of dense and long setae along lateral margins separated dorsally by barely visible bridge; posterior face pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[159,273,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3B,C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim projected posteriorly, median excavation widely open and shallow; expansions well-developed, narrow, rounded, slightly curved laterally, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view; strongly setose on apex (
<figureCitation box="[329,419,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation box="[535,622,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 slightly convex, posterior margin arched; inner angle reaching half of valvifers 9; inner margins divergent in distal half; margin dark brown. Valvulae 8 partially exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,726,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Comments.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[609,740,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[609,740,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">H. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because only these two species have paramere with posterior lobe developed and oblong and superior process of genital cup laminar and oblique to the sagittal plane (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1432,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Figs. 3B–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,220,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">5B–C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[241,379,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatum">
<emphasis box="[241,379,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">H. clavatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head of the paramere larger than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[850,981,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[850,981,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">H. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[998,1130,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Figs. 3B–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1142,1212,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">5B–C</figureCitation>
). Also, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1298,1437,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatum">
<emphasis box="[1298,1437,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">H. clavatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the superior process of the genital cup narrower and smaller than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[926,1056,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[926,1056,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">H. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species also belong to the large group of species with paramere golf club like (
<figureCitation box="[778,876,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Figs. 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[888,924,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1232,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,1232,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the golf club-like shape of the paramere (
<emphasis box="[977,1061,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">crassus</emphasis>
= thick, stout).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,789,942,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,789,942,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,942,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,465,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[203,1384,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 21. Distributional map of the new species of the H. quadridens group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777102/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[485,591,943,969]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion box="[731,784,943,969]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Pará</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
